# Lit + Vite: `accessor` keyword and the PWA plugin

`vite-plugin-pwa` runs a **secondary Rollup build** (for SW generation) that does NOT go through esbuild. If a `.ts` component file reaches that secondary build untransformed, Rollup's Acorn parser chokes on the `accessor` keyword.

## When this bites you

A component is processed raw by the secondary Rollup build when it has **no `import type`** pointing at it from any other module — i.e. it is imported only as a bare side-effect:

```ts
import './cb-board-bar.js'; // ← only import, no `import type`
```

## ✅ Safe approaches

**Option A — plain class fields** (preferred for simple components):
```ts
// ✅
@property() boardName: string = '';
@property({ type: Boolean }) isSaved: boolean = false;
```

**Option B — add an `import type`** so esbuild processes the file in the primary build:
```ts
// in coach-board.ts
import './cb-widget.js';
import type { CbWidget } from './cb-widget.js'; // ensures primary-build esbuild transform runs first
```

## ❌ Avoid

```ts
// ❌ will break the build for side-effect-only-imported components
@property() accessor boardName: string = '';
```

## Rule of thumb

If a new Lit component does **not** export any types needed by its consumers, use plain `@property()` / `@state()` class fields — not the `accessor` form.
